title: McDonald’s ends franchise partnership with  Sri Lankan operator
byline: McDonald’s Corporation and its Sri Lankan franchise partner, International Restaurant Systems (Pvt.) Ltd, have ended their business relationship, following a mutually agreed legal settlement, the companies said in a joint statement.

title: PUCSL seeks public input on CEB’s Expansion Plan for 2025-2044
byline: The Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka (PUCSL) called for a public consultation this week, to review the Long-Term Generation Expansion Plan for the Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB), covering the 2025-2044 period.

title: Sri Lanka Coconut products featured for the first time at Saudi Agriculture Expo 2024
byline: The Sri Lankan embassy in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia in collaboration with the Coconut Development Authority of Sri Lanka, successfully organized the first ever participation of ten Sri Lankan companies manufacturing coconut-based products, at the 41st edition of the Saudi Agriculture Expo 2024 held in Riyadh from October 21 to 24 2024.

title: Transgender candidate contesting an election in Sri Lanka for the first time
byline: Chanu Nimesha, the Secretary of Women’s Affairs of the Sri Lanka Socialist party, has created history by becoming the first transgender individual to contest an election in Sri Lanka.

title: Sri Lanka’s “next big step” is creditor agreement: IMF
byline: The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has acknowledged that Sri Lanka has made significant progress in implementing reforms but emphasised that the “next big step forward” is for the island nation to reach a formal agreement with all creditors.

title: Immigration authorities to crack down on overstaying Russians, Israelis
byline: The Department of Immigration and Emigration will visit the southern coastal belt in early November to look for any overstaying tourists from countries like Russia and Israel, where an influx of tourists are expected in the emerging South season for Christmas, the Daily Mirror learns.

title: Israel strikes Iran military targets amid fears of a wider war
byline: Israel said it struck military sites in Iran early on Saturday in retaliation for Tehran’s attacks on Israel earlier this month, the latest step in the escalating conflict between the heavily armed rivals.

title: Prime Minister’s Office responds to Daily Mirror report
byline: In response to Daily Mirror story headlined ‘AKD, Harini clashes over UGC Chairman appointment?’ in yesterday’s edition, the Prime Minister’s Office sent the following clarification.

title: Sajith Premadasa, SJB lead in 2024 Presidential poll campaign spending
byline: The latest financial disclosures from the Election Commission reveal that Sajith Premadasa and the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB), lead in campaign spending for the 2024 Presidential Election, with a total expenditure of Rs. 1.13 billion.

title: President hold talks with Iranian Ambassador
byline: President Anura Kumara Dissanayake met with the Iranian Ambassador, H.E. Dr. Alireza Delkhosh, today (25) at the Presidential Secretariat.

title: AASL ensures passenger, crew safety after recent bomb scares
byline: Airport and Aviation Services Sri Lanka (AASL) has reinforced its commitment to safety following two bomb threats on Vistara flights at Bandaranaike International Airport (BIA) on October 19 and October 24.

title: Inter-Club rugby to kick-off in November
byline: The Inter-Club rugby season 2024/2025 will kick-off in November with nine teams to lock horns with Sri Lions SC awaiting their debut, which was cleared by the Director General of Sports and now being forwarded to the Chairman, National Sports Council (NSC).

title: Businessmen not permitted to raise rice prices unfairly: President
byline: President Anura Kumara Dissanayake stressed that no businessman will be permitted to exploit the situation by unfairly raising the prices of rice.

title: Sri Lanka A beat Pakistan Shaheens to qualify for final
byline: Sri Lanka A beat Pakistan Shaheens by seven wickets in the first semi-final at the Oman Cricket Academy Ground in Muscat on Friday to qualify for the final of the ACC Men’s T20 Emerging Teams Asia Cup.

title: SL addressing issues raised in recent travel advisories: President
byline: Sri Lanka is addressing issues raised in recent travel advisories to maintain a secure and welcoming environment for all tourists, President Anura Kumara Dissanayake said during a meeting with two foreign envoys today.

title: Ranjan’s General Elections nomination challenged before court
byline: A Fundamental Rights petition has been filed before the Supreme Court seeking an order preventing Ranjan Ramanayake from contesting the parliamentary election scheduled for November 14.

title: Three Lebanese journalists killed in Israeli strike
byline: Three journalists have been killed in an Israeli airstrike on a building known to be housing reporters in southern Lebanon, witnesses have told the BBC.

title: SJB candidate wants probe on mudslinging against her on social media
byline: Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) Matale District candidate Rohini Kaviratne has lodged a complaint with Rattota police against what she claims is fake news that is being circulated about her over social media.

title: Election Commission to mark voters’ index fingers for 2024 General Elections
byline: The Election Commission has decided to mark the voters’ index fingers for this year’s general elections, Commissioner General Saman Ratnayake announced.

title: Dominant Sri Lanka set for easy win
byline: Unbeaten defending champions Sri Lanka will target another easy win when they confront the Maldives in their 13th Asian Senior Netball Championship 2024 Group ‘A’ encounter at the Koramangala Indoor Stadium in Bengaluru, India today at 5.00 p.m.

title: Security boosted at Pallekale Cricket Stadium and Kandy
byline: In the wake of security threats on Israelis in Sri Lanka, special security measures have been implemented, and search operations conducted by the Police and STF at the Pallekale International Cricket Stadium ahead of Sri Lanka’s practice session.

title: Tense situation at Pamunugama Police Station over alleged assault on arrested youth
byline: A tense situation was reported yesterday afternoon as local residents gathered outside the Pamunugama Police Station to protest against the alleged assault of two youths in police custody.

title: President to meet several envoys, EU delegation today
byline: President Anura Kumara Dissanayake is set to hold a series of meetings with the High Commissioners of South Africa and New Zealand, along with the Ambassadors of Iran and Myanmar, as well as a delegation from the European Union today (25) at the Presidential Secretariat.

title: IRD sets requirements for Liquor License Tax Clearance, effective January 2025
byline: The Inland Revenue Department (IRD) has informed liquor license holders to meet specific requirements when requesting Tax Clearance Certificates for license renewals, effective January 1, 2025.

title: Cricketer David Warner’s lifetime leadership ban lifted
byline: Veteran David Warner’s lifetime ban on any leadership role within Australian cricket imposed after a 2018 ball-tampering scandal was lifted Friday.

title: Three more Chinese nationals arrested over online scams
byline: Three more Chinese nationals have been arrested in connection with the online scams while staying at a hotel in Ginthota, Galle.

title: New Zealand airport puts three-minute cap on farewell hugs
byline: An airport at the bottom of New Zealand’s South Island has found itself at the center of a polarizing debate after introducing a time limit on hugs in its drop-off zone.

title: UK High Commission hopeful Sri Lanka will tackle terrorism threat soon
byline: The British High Commission in Sri Lanka expressed confidence that Sri Lankan authorities will soon address the terrorism threat, while reaffirming its support to the government.

title: Security beefed in Colombo, Weligama, Ella over possible threat
byline: The elite Special Task Force (STF) have heightened security in Colombo, Weligama and Ella as well, a day after the US Embassy in Colombo gave a warning of a possible terror threat in Arugam Bay, a senior defence source told Daily Mirror last evening.

title: Sri Lanka Tourism Alliance slams travel advisories
byline: The Sri Lanka Tourism Alliance yesterday sent a strong message to foreign embassies regarding travel advisories citing possible terrorist attacks, which could lead to serious setbacks for the local tourism sector.

title: No title
byline: No byline

title: Government plans to conduct PC elections within next year: President
byline: The government has planned to conduct the Provincial Council elections within next year, President Anura Kumara Dissanayake said today.

title: Have become a challenge to major political parties: Ranjan
byline: Actor turned politician Ranjan Ramanyake today said  major political parties have got alarmed after he decided to come back into politics.

title: Yevan David finishes third in F4 qualifying race at FIA Motorsports Games
byline: Team Sri Lanka’s Yevan David finished third in the qualifying race of the Formula Four event at the FIA Motorsports Games in Valencia, Spain, and will provisionally line up on the second row of Sunday’s medal race.

title: Student dies after reportedly jumping onto moving train
byline: A 17-year-old student of a leading government school in Colombo 7 reportedly committed suicide by jumping onto a moving train near Dematagoda Railway station, police said.

title: NPP wins big in Elpitiya Pradeshiya Sabha election
byline: The National People’s Party (NPP) has achieved a major victory in the Elpitiya Pradeshiya Sabha election held on Saturday (26).
